rooms.roomDescription: Nice to have space in a master bath, and that you will have! A seller designed stand up shower to refresh you, after a long day! Add to that, a newer latrine, pedestal sink, mirror and light just for you.,Flooring: Linoleum
Here's a full unfinished basement for you to enjoy in any way you like. Maybe let those decorative juices flow and create the rec room of your dreams!,Flooring: Concrete

Space for a cozy place to sit, look out at your back yard patio and gazebo, and stay out of the rain, or just use for storage, keeping your broom and small yard tools close at hand. Your choice but there it is, for whatever you choose!,Flooring: Carpet
Your washer will be in the bsmnt., but this can be a special room for your dryer, right off the kitchen...how convenient, for quick folding and putting those clothes away!,Flooring: Linoleum
Spacious living room with sought after LVP flooring. Amazing picture window opens up the room, adding beauty along with healthy sunlight!,Flooring: Luxury Vinyl Tile
#2 bedroom has newer LVP flooring to get you started! Plenty of design possibilities could happen here!,Flooring: Luxury Vinyl Tile
This fully renovated main floor 1/2 bath is a joy! LVP flooring, tastefully painted and designed. New everything!,Flooring: Luxury Vinyl Tile
Good sized, cozy master bedroom, painted in trendy brown shade and carpeted. Offers a cooling ceiling fan, for your comfort.,Flooring: Carpet
This bonus room can easily be used for a dining space, a family room, an office or a play room! Whatever you desire!,Flooring: Carpet

Surprise! A cute 3rd bedroom can be found, once you're in the 2nd floor full bath! Keep walking, step down, and you'll be right there...the lovely lavender paint will sure catch your eye!,Flooring: Carpet
Nothing beats a large eat-in kitchen! Counters and cupboards galore! Add to that, you'll have that breakfast bar you've been wanting!,Flooring: Linoleum

data.description: Schedule your private showing to see this beloved 3 bed, 1 1/2 bath colonial with large eat in kitchen, and full, unfinished basement, in Ashtabula, Oh. This home boasts a large covered porch in the front, for sitting in the morning or evening, sipping your favorite coffee, and in the backyard, a great patio with gazebo and fire-pit - for entertaining! Sellers have installed many updates including the much desired LVP flooring in living room, adjoining hallway, also in the very lovely, fully renovated 1/2 bath on main floor, and #2 bdrm on the second floor. You'll notice, in the living room, a beautiful picture window, which all the more opens up this already spacious room, inviting in the sun. As you go down the hall, you will notice a great BONUS room to your left! Would you use it for a dining area? A family room or an office? If you have children or babysit, it will make an amazing play room too, (as it is now being used!) Next, as you enter the kitchen you will be pleased to see how large and accomodating it is, with plenty of counter space, and so many cupboards to fill! Can you even believe it would have a nice breakfast bar too? There is so much offered in this home, yet still plenty of room to express yourself and bring your own decorating touches. Getting 1,428 sq ft of living space in this price range, is  a real blessing! Make sure to put 916 E. 15th St. in Ashtabula, on your MUST SEE list today!
